   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER TWO THE SECRET OF FEEDING</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>AND SANCTIFICATION OUTLINE The secret of feeding the continuation of regeneration the second section of God s organic salvation: The initial feeding: To feed the newborn babes new believers.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Through the cherishing of them to pray-read the word and call on the Lord by exercising their spirit cherished by Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>With the milk of the word, which is the Spirit John 6:63; Eph 6:17.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>For their growth in the divine life unto their daily salvation 1 Pet 2:2.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The continual feeding: To feed the growing believers.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>With the solid word, which is the Spirit of life Heb 5:14.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>For their maturity in the divine life unto transformation and conformation to the image of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Feeding in shepherding: Christ as the One who came that the believers may have life John 10:10b is the good Shepherd giving His life for redeeming the believers and rising up to feed His sheep with Himself as the green pasture that they may have life more abundantly vv.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>2-4, 9, 11, 14-16 .</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>He shepherds all His believers and guides them to springs of waters of life Rev 7:17.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>He as the great Shepherd shepherds God s flock in resurrection for their perfection to do God s will within them Heb 13:20-21.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>He is the Shepherd of the believers soul within the believers to oversee them 1 Pet 2:25.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>He is the Chief Shepherd who will reward the faithful elders, who shepherd God s flock faithfully, with the unfading crown of glory for their encouragement 1 Pet 5:4.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>He commissioned Peter, the apostle appointed by Him, to feed His lambs and shepherd His sheep in his loving of Him John 21:15-17.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>He as the Head gives the Body gifted persons, one kind of which are the shepherds, who perfect the saints by teaching for the building up of the Body of Christ Eph 4:11-12.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The main responsibility of the elders in the church is to shepherd God s flock by teaching faithfully 1 Pet 5:2-3; 1 Tim 3:2; 5:17.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The elders shepherding of the church, the flock of God, is the best way to take care of the fierce wolves and those speaking perverted things among the churches Acts 20:28-30.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The secret of sanctification the third section of God s organic salvation: God s sanctification of the believers is of three aspects: The first aspect is the seeking sanctification by the Holy Spirit with the enlightening word initially 1 Pet 1:2; Luke 15:8.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The second aspect is the positional sanctification by the redeeming blood of Christ judicially Heb 13:12; 10:29.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>The third aspect is the dispositional sanctification by the Holy Spirit organically Rom 15:16; 6:19, 22.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>We are created by God in the particular sense that we are for Him.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>But we became fallen from God, and we were lost in our position standing and in our nature disposition , becoming common.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Hence, in saving us, God sanctified us both in our position, in our standing before Him, outwardly and judicially, and in our fallen disposition inwardly and organically.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>We have covered God s positional and judicial sanctification on other occasions.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>What is covered in this message is God s dispositional and organic sanctification: By the Holy Spirit Rom 15:16: In their disposition.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>With the divine, holy nature of God 2 Pet 1:4 that they may be holy unto God Eph 1:4 .</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>With the element of the resurrection life of Christ, which they received through the feeding.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>From their spirit captivated by Christ, through their soul, and unto their body, so that their entire being can be wholly sanctified 1 Thes 5:23.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Since all the believers will be the components of the holy city, New Jerusalem, all of them should be sanctified to be as holy as the HOLY CITY, the New Jerusalem.</S>
   </TEXT>
